1
00:00:57,474 --> 00:01:01,019
THE WONDERFOOLS

2
00:01:02,187 --> 00:01:06,816
EPISODE 8
THE GUARDIANS OF HAESEONG CITY PART 2

3
00:01:09,819 --> 00:01:11,946
Kim Pal-ho, our shepherd,

4
00:01:12,447 --> 00:01:14,282
has been martyred.

5
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:20,830
Shepherd!

6
00:01:22,749 --> 00:01:24,334
What do we do, Eun Chae-ni?

7
00:01:24,834 --> 00:01:26,669
We're all doomed now.

8
00:01:29,172 --> 00:01:33,343
I may be broke and pathetic,
but I'm still a father and a husband.

9
00:01:33,426 --> 00:01:35,011
The head of my family.

10
00:01:36,054 --> 00:01:39,474
My dear Cheong is only 14 years old.

11
00:01:40,433 --> 00:01:44,145
Had I known an apocalypse was coming,
I would've bought her that CD player,

12
00:01:44,229 --> 00:01:46,689
even if it meant being
up to my eyeballs in debt.

13
00:01:47,190 --> 00:01:49,192
What are you crying for?

14
00:01:49,692 --> 00:01:51,111
You could've just said that.

15
00:01:51,194 --> 00:01:52,695
Would that change anything?

16
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:54,531
What could we even do?

17
00:01:54,614 --> 00:01:58,284
They're Wunderkinder,
and apparently, we're just defective.

18
00:01:58,993 --> 00:02:00,036
You're right.

19
00:02:00,537 --> 00:02:02,997
Saying it wouldn't change anything.

20
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:07,043
So tie your shoelaces tight and get ready

21
00:02:07,544 --> 00:02:08,378
to run.

22
00:02:08,461 --> 00:02:09,337
What…

23
00:02:26,855 --> 00:02:27,730
Stay back!

24
00:02:28,231 --> 00:02:29,274
Stay back!

25
00:02:29,774 --> 00:02:31,276
I'll slice you up!

26
00:02:31,359 --> 00:02:32,652
She'll slice you up!

27
00:02:32,735 --> 00:02:34,070
I'm Lady Trainwreck!

28
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:35,905
I'm Royal Nightmare!

29
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,116
Stay back!

30
00:02:39,325 --> 00:02:41,244
Stop right there! Stay back!

31
00:02:41,828 --> 00:02:44,497
Hey, Eun Chae-ni.
Take us somewhere else, anywhere!

32
00:02:45,248 --> 00:02:46,666
I'd love to,

33
00:02:46,749 --> 00:02:50,170
but I ate my last coffee jelly
to save Ro-bin.

34
00:02:53,464 --> 00:02:57,260
I really hoped I'd get a chance
to say goodbye to Moon Mi-hui and Cheong.

35
00:02:57,343 --> 00:02:58,386
Mr. Son.

36
00:02:58,469 --> 00:02:59,888
Forget it. Don't comfort me!

37
00:03:04,726 --> 00:03:06,311
Just my luck, I guess.

38
00:03:07,145 --> 00:03:10,273
I worked my ass off
only to get treated like an ass.

39
00:03:10,356 --> 00:03:11,774
The world's screwed up.

40
00:03:11,858 --> 00:03:14,319
Was the financial crisis my fault?

41
00:03:14,402 --> 00:03:16,571
Is it my fault my company restructured?

42
00:03:16,654 --> 00:03:18,323
I'm a victim too.

43
00:03:18,823 --> 00:03:21,326
Why am I always treated like a loser?

44
00:03:21,409 --> 00:03:22,660
I don't ask for much!

45
00:03:22,744 --> 00:03:24,370
Why am I always--

46
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:38,635
Finally, some peace and quiet.

47
00:03:38,718 --> 00:03:40,303
It was a bit noisy, wasn't it?

48
00:03:41,054 --> 00:03:43,765
He's not such a bad guy
once you get to know him.

49
00:03:44,265 --> 00:03:46,226
He just likes to talk big.

50
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:57,737
SON GYEONG-HUN
MOON MI-HUI

51
00:04:01,658 --> 00:04:03,368
Chae-ni, you little shit.

52
00:04:03,451 --> 00:04:04,786
Alrighty, then.

53
00:04:04,869 --> 00:04:06,955
Who's going to come at me first?

54
00:04:07,038 --> 00:04:08,373
Hotteok lady?

55
00:04:08,456 --> 00:04:10,166
Or Mr. Heo from the general store?

56
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,293
You're going to get hurt.

57
00:04:12,377 --> 00:04:14,629
I wonder if you'll be all right with that.

58
00:04:14,712 --> 00:04:16,631
One wrong move and you lose a finger.

59
00:04:16,714 --> 00:04:18,424
Then who'd flip the hotteok?

60
00:04:22,845 --> 00:04:23,680
Get her.

61
00:04:26,057 --> 00:04:27,976
Hold up. Stay back!

62
00:04:28,059 --> 00:04:29,310
Don't you dare touch me!

63
00:04:29,394 --> 00:04:30,812
There are too damn many!

64
00:04:30,895 --> 00:04:32,105
You'll get hurt!

65
00:04:32,188 --> 00:04:33,564
Let go, damn it!

66
00:04:33,648 --> 00:04:35,441
I told you not to. Why are you--

67
00:04:37,485 --> 00:04:38,736
What do you want with me?

68
00:04:50,248 --> 00:04:51,416
Outsiders!

69
00:04:51,499 --> 00:04:53,126
Let's protect our temple!

70
00:04:53,209 --> 00:04:54,544
Charge!

71
00:05:24,824 --> 00:05:26,159
What the… What was that?

72
00:05:26,242 --> 00:05:28,119
Everyone, freeze!

73
00:05:29,078 --> 00:05:31,539
Get away from my granddaughter!

74
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:33,374
Grandma?

75
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:36,002
Eunie!

76
00:05:37,003 --> 00:05:38,046
Grandma!

77
00:05:38,129 --> 00:05:39,047
Take this.

78
00:05:39,547 --> 00:05:40,381
Are you okay?

79
00:05:48,431 --> 00:05:51,684
Look at you.
Did you crawl out of a dumpster?

80
00:05:53,311 --> 00:05:55,730
Grandma, look at yourself first.

81
00:05:55,813 --> 00:05:58,149
Did you not sleep at all last night?

82
00:05:58,232 --> 00:06:01,235
Look at the bags under your eyes.
You'll collapse at this rate!

83
00:06:03,654 --> 00:06:05,073
The owner of Hearty House?

84
00:06:07,241 --> 00:06:08,534
What brings

85
00:06:09,827 --> 00:06:10,953
you here?

86
00:06:40,483 --> 00:06:41,484
There you are.

87
00:06:42,693 --> 00:06:44,779
I thought you would have gone
to see your mom.

88
00:06:47,031 --> 00:06:48,032
Why us?

89
00:06:49,867 --> 00:06:52,412
I'm just curious why you did
those awful things to us.

90
00:06:52,495 --> 00:06:54,831
There's no particular reason.

91
00:06:55,706 --> 00:06:57,083
All of this started

92
00:06:57,166 --> 00:07:02,547
with humanity's petty desire
to live a long life.

93
00:07:04,048 --> 00:07:05,675
That's how the world works.

94
00:07:08,761 --> 00:07:11,013
Things that may look grand on the outside

95
00:07:11,097 --> 00:07:12,140
often come from

96
00:07:12,849 --> 00:07:15,935
petty greed, petty envy,

97
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:19,063
and the most trivial of discoveries.

98
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:24,026
We needed children
to experiment on back then,

99
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:26,362
and you just happened to be one of them.

100
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:27,864
So,

101
00:07:28,448 --> 00:07:30,825
don't seek reason or meaning.

102
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:33,077
There is none.

103
00:07:33,828 --> 00:07:37,623
Life merely exists

104
00:07:38,124 --> 00:07:41,669
upon banal coincidences and petty reasons

105
00:07:41,752 --> 00:07:43,296
until we eventually perish.

106
00:07:44,839 --> 00:07:45,923
Petty?

107
00:07:48,593 --> 00:07:50,553
I guess human lives are trivial to you.

108
00:07:50,636 --> 00:07:53,556
Out of the 72 children,

109
00:07:54,223 --> 00:07:55,808
50% of them manifested,

110
00:07:55,892 --> 00:07:59,604
and half of those who manifested
gained abilities.

111
00:08:00,104 --> 00:08:04,066
One of them was the child
with the Heart of Eternity.

112
00:08:04,609 --> 00:08:07,945
That child was the only
meaningful end product.

113
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:14,535
So I thought

114
00:08:15,536 --> 00:08:18,831
if more people manifested,

115
00:08:19,582 --> 00:08:22,376
then wouldn't the number
of eternal hearts also increase

116
00:08:23,044 --> 00:08:24,378
at a similar probability?

117
00:08:26,088 --> 00:08:27,673
Enough with the riddles.

118
00:08:45,983 --> 00:08:46,859
Are you saying

119
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:49,445
you'll unleash that drug on Haeseong?

120
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:52,323
God sometimes brings destruction and chaos

121
00:08:52,406 --> 00:08:54,116
to create a new order.

122
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:55,535
Are you

123
00:08:56,619 --> 00:08:57,495
actually insane?

124
00:08:59,372 --> 00:09:01,457
What about the children who died?

125
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:03,668
Among the children experimented on,

126
00:09:04,293 --> 00:09:06,379
half died without ever manifesting.

127
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:09,590
And of those who manifested,

128
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:13,010
some died from the physical mutations.

129
00:09:14,011 --> 00:09:16,973
Far more children died
than the few who survived.

130
00:09:21,894 --> 00:09:25,064
For a single coincidence
that may or may not recur,

131
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:28,568
you're going to kill
all those people again?

132
00:09:28,651 --> 00:09:32,572
It's not the dead children
who change history.

133
00:09:33,197 --> 00:09:34,824
It's you, the survivors.

134
00:09:37,827 --> 00:09:39,161
You actual son of a bitch.

135
00:09:44,625 --> 00:09:46,669
Bring me the Child of Eternity again.

136
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:52,049
Let us create a new order
in a new world together.

137
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:55,970
Ko Eun-san.

138
00:09:57,054 --> 00:09:59,307
You will become a new breed of humans.

139
00:10:04,186 --> 00:10:06,564
On my way here, I wondered…

140
00:10:09,358 --> 00:10:10,276
if I…

141
00:10:14,322 --> 00:10:15,906
could kill you.

142
00:10:44,685 --> 00:10:46,020
A pity.

143
00:10:46,729 --> 00:10:48,773
I was quite fond of you.

144
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:35,319
Father.

145
00:11:54,672 --> 00:11:55,881
Father!

146
00:12:17,361 --> 00:12:18,404
Master.

147
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:21,031
Grandma.

148
00:12:22,158 --> 00:12:23,284
Handle things here.

149
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:25,244
What about you?

150
00:12:25,953 --> 00:12:27,747
I don't know if it'll work,

151
00:12:28,330 --> 00:12:29,915
but I really need it to.

152
00:12:30,624 --> 00:12:31,834
Please, let's go.

153
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:33,711
To Master.

154
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:35,296
Please!

155
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:52,813
Hot!

156
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:54,648
What the… Fire!

157
00:12:56,567 --> 00:12:59,153
Master!

158
00:13:03,949 --> 00:13:04,784
Master?

159
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:09,622
Oh dear, this isn't the right face.

160
00:13:09,705 --> 00:13:11,081
It's not the right face.

161
00:13:14,043 --> 00:13:17,004
This isn't the face I'm looking for.
I can't save you.

162
00:13:18,339 --> 00:13:19,256
Master!

163
00:13:22,051 --> 00:13:23,093
Help me.

164
00:13:23,177 --> 00:13:25,888
Master's face doesn't look like this.

165
00:13:25,971 --> 00:13:26,889
I'm sorry.

166
00:13:30,768 --> 00:13:32,102
Damn it.

167
00:13:36,357 --> 00:13:38,025
Chae-ni, my God--

168
00:13:46,408 --> 00:13:47,409
Call 119!

169
00:13:50,579 --> 00:13:52,790
Answer me! Damn, that's hot!

170
00:13:52,873 --> 00:13:54,124
Master!

171
00:14:03,676 --> 00:14:07,054
Eunie, that's enough.

172
00:14:07,555 --> 00:14:10,266
We just called 119.

173
00:14:11,934 --> 00:14:13,269
Grandma, he's not there.

174
00:14:16,272 --> 00:14:17,773
Master.

175
00:14:20,359 --> 00:14:21,861
I can't find him.

176
00:15:13,162 --> 00:15:14,204
Father.

177
00:15:14,288 --> 00:15:16,040
Father, it's me. Father?

178
00:16:24,608 --> 00:16:25,818
Hey, Ju-ran.

179
00:16:26,527 --> 00:16:28,612
We'll be in downtown Haeseong
in 15 minutes.

180
00:16:30,406 --> 00:16:31,281
All right.

181
00:16:31,782 --> 00:16:33,701
Don't let anything go wrong.

182
00:16:34,201 --> 00:16:35,619
No matter what happens…

183
00:16:38,372 --> 00:16:39,456
stick to the plan.

184
00:16:40,958 --> 00:16:41,917
Ju-ran.

185
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:45,129
Everything's okay, right?

186
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:51,844
Yeah.

187
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:54,013
Everything's fine.

188
00:16:54,596 --> 00:16:56,140
When's Pal-ho joining us?

189
00:16:58,809 --> 00:17:00,686
Pal-ho can't make it, Ho-ran.

190
00:17:02,312 --> 00:17:03,939
I'll send someone else instead.

191
00:17:05,649 --> 00:17:06,483
Who?

192
00:18:00,245 --> 00:18:02,039
I'm sorry about back then.

193
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:03,874
Sir!

194
00:18:03,957 --> 00:18:05,417
Please open this door.

195
00:18:06,919 --> 00:18:09,254
Sir, please!

196
00:18:09,338 --> 00:18:10,547
Sir!

197
00:18:10,631 --> 00:18:12,091
Sir!

198
00:18:13,550 --> 00:18:17,137
The debt I owe you from back then,
let me settle it now.

199
00:18:19,181 --> 00:18:20,933
The door is wide open now,

200
00:18:21,433 --> 00:18:24,937
so go and live your life to the fullest.

201
00:18:25,813 --> 00:18:26,939
Okay?

202
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:42,037
Number 3972.

203
00:18:43,163 --> 00:18:44,248
Can you hear me?

204
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:47,459
Number 3972.

205
00:18:56,051 --> 00:18:57,803
Yeah, okay. Bye.

206
00:18:57,886 --> 00:18:58,762
Grandma.

207
00:19:01,014 --> 00:19:02,933
One of the believers says

208
00:19:03,016 --> 00:19:06,311
two container trucks headed downtown
early this morning.

209
00:19:07,271 --> 00:19:08,689
What was loaded in them?

210
00:19:08,772 --> 00:19:10,941
I don't know the details.

211
00:19:11,608 --> 00:19:13,777
I just saw them leave early this morning.

212
00:19:17,364 --> 00:19:18,740
They're loaded with a drug.

213
00:19:20,033 --> 00:19:21,952
Royal Nightmare said he saw it.

214
00:19:22,035 --> 00:19:24,121
They're planning to spray it
all over Haeseong.

215
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:28,041
Should we report it?

216
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:29,376
There's no point.

217
00:19:30,377 --> 00:19:32,045
That bastard, Byeong-jin,

218
00:19:32,129 --> 00:19:34,756
is already under the influence
of the Church.

219
00:19:36,049 --> 00:19:37,801
I'd better meet the mayor first.

220
00:19:37,885 --> 00:19:39,595
That won't be necessary.

221
00:19:43,056 --> 00:19:44,266
Holy Mother.

222
00:19:44,808 --> 00:19:46,685
Holy Mother.

223
00:19:47,186 --> 00:19:48,770
Holy Mother.

224
00:20:02,784 --> 00:20:04,328
Are you another one of those kids?

225
00:20:12,669 --> 00:20:14,213
You look badly hurt.

226
00:20:14,296 --> 00:20:15,297
Don't move.

227
00:20:17,758 --> 00:20:21,261
Hey, Mr. Gu, are you insane?
What do you think you're doing?

228
00:20:24,097 --> 00:20:26,808
Stop it.
Don't mess with Grandma or Mr. Gu.

229
00:20:26,892 --> 00:20:30,812
If you have something to say,
say it to me. Don't mess with my family!

230
00:20:33,315 --> 00:20:35,317
I already lost my brother

231
00:20:36,276 --> 00:20:37,361
and my father.

232
00:20:40,864 --> 00:20:42,574
Now it's your turn.

233
00:20:42,658 --> 00:20:43,575
No!

234
00:20:50,207 --> 00:20:51,959
She'll be back.

235
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:54,711
The moment she shows up,

236
00:20:55,921 --> 00:20:56,755
shoot her.

237
00:21:10,477 --> 00:21:13,522
If you want to live, move!

238
00:21:20,529 --> 00:21:21,863
I said move!

239
00:21:27,536 --> 00:21:29,246
Chae-ni, you're so freaking cool.

240
00:21:29,746 --> 00:21:31,248
Here goes!

241
00:21:35,752 --> 00:21:36,753
Here I go.

242
00:21:38,588 --> 00:21:40,215
Yeah!

243
00:21:40,841 --> 00:21:43,218
Eun Chae-ni, coming through!

244
00:21:45,637 --> 00:21:47,014
Now! Get her out!

245
00:21:59,985 --> 00:22:01,194
So refreshing.

246
00:22:33,518 --> 00:22:34,394
Cheong.

247
00:22:39,524 --> 00:22:40,359
What about Dad?

248
00:22:41,735 --> 00:22:43,653
Don't worry about it, honey.

249
00:22:45,447 --> 00:22:49,785
How dare he stay out all night.
At this point, he's asking for a divorce.

250
00:22:50,952 --> 00:22:52,037
You're divorcing?

251
00:22:53,955 --> 00:22:58,043
Don't worry about anything
and just focus on the rehearsal, okay?

252
00:22:58,668 --> 00:22:59,795
Stand up straight!

253
00:23:00,587 --> 00:23:02,089
Honey, say cheese!

254
00:23:07,511 --> 00:23:10,555
Please just gather around for a moment.
Thank you, everyone.

255
00:23:10,639 --> 00:23:11,765
Thank you all so much.

256
00:23:11,848 --> 00:23:15,018
I'm so grateful to see you
working so hard. Hello, Mayor.

257
00:23:17,437 --> 00:23:22,442
Tonight's parade will start
exactly at eleven o'clock as planned.

258
00:23:22,526 --> 00:23:25,362
As we rehearsed,
the order will be as follows.

259
00:23:25,445 --> 00:23:29,324
First, the flag bearers,
then the marching band will follow.

260
00:23:29,408 --> 00:23:31,535
Then, the Changwon Samulnori Troupe will--

261
00:23:31,618 --> 00:23:33,537
Everybody, stop!

262
00:23:34,121 --> 00:23:35,414
Everyone!

263
00:23:35,497 --> 00:23:37,541
- Who, why? What is it?
- Everyone, stop!

264
00:23:37,624 --> 00:23:40,710
Stop what you're doing, all of you,
and get out of here!

265
00:23:40,794 --> 00:23:42,087
Everybody stop!

266
00:23:43,088 --> 00:23:45,006
Stop what you're doing
and get out of here.

267
00:23:45,715 --> 00:23:46,675
You can't stay here.

268
00:23:46,758 --> 00:23:48,635
- Why not?
- You can't stay here!

269
00:23:49,302 --> 00:23:51,012
What's going on, huh?

270
00:23:51,096 --> 00:23:54,266
Honey! What are you doing over there?

271
00:23:55,475 --> 00:23:56,351
Honey!

272
00:23:57,853 --> 00:23:58,728
Honey!

273
00:23:58,812 --> 00:24:00,522
Honey!

274
00:24:01,606 --> 00:24:02,774
You're here too?

275
00:24:03,942 --> 00:24:05,819
Cheong!

276
00:24:05,902 --> 00:24:07,279
My darling Cheong as well?

277
00:24:07,362 --> 00:24:08,530
Cheong!

278
00:24:09,239 --> 00:24:10,490
You can't stay here.

279
00:24:10,574 --> 00:24:13,618
Honey, come with me.
We have to go. This isn't a drill!

280
00:24:13,702 --> 00:24:17,956
Why on earth are you doing this
in front of all these people?

281
00:24:18,039 --> 00:24:21,168
That's how urgent and dangerous
the situation is. Let's go, now!

282
00:24:21,751 --> 00:24:24,713
- Let's go!
- Go where?

283
00:24:24,796 --> 00:24:26,798
Do you know how long
she's waited for today?

284
00:24:26,882 --> 00:24:29,718
She was chosen to represent her grade,
not just her class.

285
00:24:29,801 --> 00:24:31,303
What would you know?

286
00:24:31,386 --> 00:24:34,431
Being the damn grade representative
doesn't matter right now!

287
00:24:35,765 --> 00:24:37,559
The apocalypse is coming!

288
00:24:37,642 --> 00:24:38,643
Seriously?

289
00:24:40,145 --> 00:24:41,563
Screw the new millennium!

290
00:24:42,189 --> 00:24:44,566
Everything will disappear in an instant!

291
00:24:45,942 --> 00:24:48,445
If you keep embarrassing me like this,

292
00:24:48,945 --> 00:24:50,363
you'll be the one to disappear.

293
00:24:51,781 --> 00:24:53,450
From Cheong's life and mine.

294
00:24:53,950 --> 00:24:54,784
Forever.

295
00:24:57,287 --> 00:24:58,872
- Honey.
- Stop embarrassing me!

296
00:24:58,955 --> 00:25:00,457
Honey, you have to listen to me!

297
00:25:02,501 --> 00:25:03,627
- Come on.
- Mr. Yang.

298
00:25:04,377 --> 00:25:05,295
Listen to me!

299
00:25:06,213 --> 00:25:08,465
Please tell everyone to evacuate.

300
00:25:08,548 --> 00:25:10,675
The guys at the Church
of Eternal Salvation.

301
00:25:10,759 --> 00:25:13,136
Do you know what they're trying to do
to Haeseong?

302
00:25:13,220 --> 00:25:14,721
I do.

303
00:25:16,223 --> 00:25:17,474
You do?

304
00:25:17,557 --> 00:25:20,435
They donated a whopping 100 million won
for this festival.

305
00:25:20,519 --> 00:25:22,896
Thanks to them,
we were able to make a giant version

306
00:25:22,979 --> 00:25:24,481
of our city mascot, Yang-soon,

307
00:25:24,564 --> 00:25:27,275
and even have a fireworks show tonight.

308
00:25:27,359 --> 00:25:29,528
It's all just a cover!

309
00:25:29,611 --> 00:25:32,030
You mustn't fall for it!

310
00:25:32,531 --> 00:25:35,450
Please just listen to me!

311
00:25:36,076 --> 00:25:37,285
Damn it, that hurts!

312
00:25:37,369 --> 00:25:41,289
First you said that a pigeon
blinked its eyes sideways like this,

313
00:25:41,373 --> 00:25:43,291
then a carp this big winked at you.

314
00:25:43,375 --> 00:25:45,544
That it was because of phenol
and dumped waste,

315
00:25:45,627 --> 00:25:48,088
and now you're blaming it on the Church?

316
00:25:48,171 --> 00:25:49,881
- That's right!
- Fine, okay.

317
00:25:49,965 --> 00:25:52,926
For matters like these,
go ahead and file a complaint,

318
00:25:53,009 --> 00:25:54,469
but please hold off for today.

319
00:25:54,553 --> 00:25:56,304
It's a festival, after all.

320
00:25:56,388 --> 00:26:00,642
The anticipated new millennium is upon us.
You can't rain on our parade like this.

321
00:26:00,725 --> 00:26:03,728
Your daughter is even a flag bearer.

322
00:26:03,812 --> 00:26:04,813
Cut it out.

323
00:26:04,896 --> 00:26:06,690
Just call the police.

324
00:26:06,773 --> 00:26:09,651
Royal Nightmare can't stand to see
other people happy.

325
00:26:09,734 --> 00:26:11,194
- All right.
- Always grumbling.

326
00:26:11,278 --> 00:26:13,738
- Come on now.
- He's always complaining.

327
00:26:14,239 --> 00:26:17,409
I'll take care of it. I will.

328
00:26:17,492 --> 00:26:18,326
Cheong.

329
00:26:18,827 --> 00:26:21,663
Goodness, isn't he embarrassed
in front of his daughter?

330
00:26:21,746 --> 00:26:23,707
- Exactly!
- That's a bit harsh.

331
00:26:23,790 --> 00:26:25,584
His daughter is here listening, so…

332
00:26:38,513 --> 00:26:39,431
Mr. Son?

333
00:26:44,769 --> 00:26:45,604
Chae-ni!

334
00:26:59,034 --> 00:27:02,162
Master is gone,
and Grandma isn't here either.

335
00:27:03,496 --> 00:27:04,706
What do we do now?

336
00:27:04,789 --> 00:27:06,124
What do you mean?

337
00:27:07,667 --> 00:27:10,837
We'll face the apocalypse
like this, together.

338
00:27:22,932 --> 00:27:26,770
Should we just run away by ourselves?
What a load of nonsense!

339
00:27:26,853 --> 00:27:29,814
How could I leave Moon Mi-hui
and Cheong behind? Are you mad?

340
00:27:36,237 --> 00:27:38,156
Chae-ni, what are we going to do?

341
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:39,949
Come to think of it,

342
00:27:40,450 --> 00:27:43,036
I never got to take a picture with Master.

343
00:27:43,119 --> 00:27:44,245
Excuse me?

344
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:47,957
How can you talk about pictures
at a time like this?

345
00:27:48,458 --> 00:27:50,210
The apocalypse is coming for Haeseong!

346
00:27:50,293 --> 00:27:53,463
You, me, everyone. We'll all be wiped out.

347
00:27:54,464 --> 00:27:56,466
We're the only ones who know that,

348
00:27:56,549 --> 00:27:59,052
but there's nothing
we can do about it. Why?

349
00:27:59,552 --> 00:28:02,555
Because no one believes us. Why?

350
00:28:05,141 --> 00:28:07,477
Because we're nobodies.

351
00:28:12,899 --> 00:28:14,109
REWARD GRAPES

352
00:28:14,192 --> 00:28:15,485
GREAT JOB

353
00:28:25,412 --> 00:28:26,955
First, let's stop the trucks.

354
00:28:27,038 --> 00:28:28,164
What trucks?

355
00:28:28,957 --> 00:28:31,459
The trucks with the drug
are somewhere in Haeseong.

356
00:28:31,543 --> 00:28:33,503
They're going to blow it up somewhere.

357
00:28:33,586 --> 00:28:35,213
Where exactly?

358
00:28:35,296 --> 00:28:36,715
Where else?

359
00:28:36,798 --> 00:28:39,926
The place where the most people
are gathered in Haeseong right now.

360
00:28:42,429 --> 00:28:43,930
Where do you think?

361
00:28:45,515 --> 00:28:46,766
- Where?
- Where?

362
00:28:48,435 --> 00:28:50,937
- Sorry, excuse us.
- Move.

363
00:28:51,020 --> 00:28:52,355
- Why's it so crowded?
- Please.

364
00:28:52,439 --> 00:28:54,607
- Move.
- The mascot of Haeseong!

365
00:28:54,691 --> 00:28:55,900
- Too crowded!
- Yang-soon.

366
00:28:55,984 --> 00:28:57,277
Buy a Yang-soon T-shirt!

367
00:28:57,360 --> 00:28:58,862
Look at Yang-soon!

368
00:28:58,945 --> 00:29:00,238
Hey, isn't that Chae-ni?

369
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:05,660
Have you seen any
Church of Eternal Salvation trucks?

370
00:29:06,494 --> 00:29:07,370
No, we haven't.

371
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:11,124
Leave Haeseong right now, okay?

372
00:29:11,207 --> 00:29:12,333
Or you'll all die!

373
00:29:12,417 --> 00:29:13,543
You'll die!

374
00:29:13,626 --> 00:29:15,170
- Leave Haeseong.
- What did she say?

375
00:29:15,253 --> 00:29:16,171
- Die?
- Leave!

376
00:29:16,254 --> 00:29:17,797
What is she talking about?

377
00:29:17,881 --> 00:29:19,215
This tastes awful.

378
00:29:19,799 --> 00:29:21,843
What kind of truck is this? What kind?

379
00:29:22,343 --> 00:29:24,387
Are you from the Church? What's in here?

380
00:29:24,471 --> 00:29:26,806
- What is this woman doing?
- Guess not. Pass.

381
00:29:26,890 --> 00:29:28,641
- Welcome.
- Okay!

382
00:29:35,398 --> 00:29:36,691
Who are you?

383
00:29:38,943 --> 00:29:39,903
What are you doing?

384
00:29:39,986 --> 00:29:42,071
You're clueless!

385
00:29:42,155 --> 00:29:43,198
What's he saying?

386
00:29:43,281 --> 00:29:46,576
I did touch the goods,
but there's something really important--

387
00:29:46,659 --> 00:29:47,827
Hey, shut it.

388
00:29:47,911 --> 00:29:50,538
By the looks of you,
you're a repeat offender.

389
00:29:50,622 --> 00:29:52,957
- Why I oughta…
- Don't judge me based on my looks--

390
00:29:53,041 --> 00:29:53,917
Ro-bin!

391
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:55,376
You don't even have a clue!

392
00:29:55,460 --> 00:29:56,711
What the heck, man!

393
00:29:57,337 --> 00:29:59,339
You got your ass kicked already?

394
00:30:00,548 --> 00:30:02,258
This is so exhausting.

395
00:30:04,093 --> 00:30:07,430
Why are we even going to such lengths?

396
00:30:07,514 --> 00:30:09,015
We have to save the people.

397
00:30:09,098 --> 00:30:12,185
Why are we responsible for the lives
of people we don't even know?

398
00:30:13,269 --> 00:30:14,437
True.

399
00:30:14,938 --> 00:30:17,065
We don't have to save people
we don't know.

400
00:30:17,148 --> 00:30:18,233
Right?

401
00:30:19,317 --> 00:30:20,860
But we know everyone here.

402
00:30:22,612 --> 00:30:23,446
Look.

403
00:30:27,992 --> 00:30:29,744
We really do know everyone here.

404
00:30:29,828 --> 00:30:32,372
Let's help the less fortunate.

405
00:30:32,455 --> 00:30:33,331
So what do we do?

406
00:30:33,414 --> 00:30:35,291
- Hello.
- Wishing you good health.

407
00:30:35,792 --> 00:30:36,668
Yes, hello.

408
00:30:36,751 --> 00:30:39,254
- Long time, no see.
- Yes, take care.

409
00:30:39,337 --> 00:30:43,758
We don't even have friends,
so how do we know so many people?

410
00:30:44,717 --> 00:30:47,804
Stop grumbling.
Let's hurry up and find them.

411
00:30:47,887 --> 00:30:49,472
We don't have time!

412
00:30:49,556 --> 00:30:50,807
Okay? Just go!

413
00:30:54,686 --> 00:30:57,021
- They're here!
- I think they're here!

414
00:30:57,105 --> 00:30:58,523
- The parade!
- You're right.

415
00:30:58,606 --> 00:31:00,149
What is it?

416
00:31:00,233 --> 00:31:01,901
- What is that?
- What?

417
00:31:01,985 --> 00:31:03,111
Where are they?

418
00:31:04,571 --> 00:31:05,530
Cheong.

419
00:31:06,614 --> 00:31:07,448
Cheong.

420
00:31:07,532 --> 00:31:11,119
ADIEU 1999, TOWARD THE YEAR 2000
A NEW MILLENNIUM, A NEW HOPE

421
00:31:23,172 --> 00:31:25,049
MILLENNIUM GRAND FESTIVAL
HAESEONG 2000

422
00:31:45,695 --> 00:31:48,531
One, two. One, two, three, four.

423
00:31:48,615 --> 00:31:50,867
One, two, three.

424
00:31:51,951 --> 00:31:53,995
- Chae-ni, wait up.
- Hurry!

425
00:31:54,078 --> 00:31:55,204
I said wait.

426
00:31:56,539 --> 00:31:58,166
- One second.
- Still so unfit.

427
00:31:58,249 --> 00:31:59,834
Why? What is it?

428
00:32:06,215 --> 00:32:07,300
Master?

429
00:32:09,636 --> 00:32:11,137
You escaped?

430
00:32:11,638 --> 00:32:12,889
When?

431
00:32:12,972 --> 00:32:14,557
How?

432
00:32:14,641 --> 00:32:17,018
I'm so glad you're safe.
I knew you would be, Master.

433
00:32:17,101 --> 00:32:19,437
I knew you would be, Master.

434
00:32:28,196 --> 00:32:30,239
- Master.
- Master?

435
00:32:30,323 --> 00:32:31,908
What'd you do that for?

436
00:32:57,767 --> 00:33:01,104
I thought words were the only thing
that could hurt me.

437
00:33:02,897 --> 00:33:06,275
I'm really upset right now, Master.
You know that?

438
00:33:12,407 --> 00:33:14,075
There is nothing…

439
00:33:16,244 --> 00:33:17,787
you can do.

440
00:33:42,145 --> 00:33:44,397
There she is. There's my daughter.

441
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:47,150
Cheong!

442
00:33:48,901 --> 00:33:49,736
Cheong!

443
00:34:07,962 --> 00:34:09,505
My daughter's awesome.

444
00:34:11,257 --> 00:34:12,508
So freaking fabulous.

445
00:34:22,226 --> 00:34:23,603
Don't worry, Cheong.

446
00:34:26,647 --> 00:34:30,485
I'll do whatever it takes to stop them.

447
00:34:31,235 --> 00:34:33,321
- Stop what?
- You scared me! Honey.

448
00:34:33,404 --> 00:34:35,823
Why don't you stop blocking the road?

449
00:34:35,907 --> 00:34:38,451
We need to reserve a good spot
to see the fireworks.

450
00:34:38,534 --> 00:34:40,495
- We can't go to see the fireworks.
- Move.

451
00:34:40,578 --> 00:34:42,914
- Honey, please.
- I need to claim a good spot.

452
00:34:45,166 --> 00:34:46,584
The fireworks.

453
00:34:47,376 --> 00:34:50,254
Do you know what the Church
is trying to do to Haeseong?

454
00:34:50,338 --> 00:34:51,172
I do.

455
00:34:51,255 --> 00:34:54,175
They donated a whopping 100 million won
for this festival.

456
00:34:54,258 --> 00:34:56,594
Thanks to them,
we were able to make a giant version

457
00:34:56,677 --> 00:34:58,179
of our city mascot, Yang-soon,

458
00:34:58,262 --> 00:35:00,681
and even have a fireworks show tonight.

459
00:35:02,600 --> 00:35:04,477
That's it. The fireworks.

460
00:35:06,395 --> 00:35:08,106
Up in the sky, in one go.

461
00:35:12,777 --> 00:35:13,611
Boom!

462
00:35:24,330 --> 00:35:25,456
Cheong!

463
00:35:26,082 --> 00:35:29,377
Honey!

464
00:35:39,178 --> 00:35:40,930
Honey!

465
00:35:41,013 --> 00:35:42,390
- Are you okay?
- Honey!

466
00:35:42,473 --> 00:35:44,767
- Are you okay? Cheong!
- Where's Cheong?

467
00:35:45,268 --> 00:35:47,353
Don't come here. Run!

468
00:35:47,436 --> 00:35:48,604
Get behind me.

469
00:35:50,189 --> 00:35:51,732
Are you okay?

470
00:35:51,816 --> 00:35:53,860
Are you okay? Move!

471
00:35:54,652 --> 00:35:56,529
Come this way.

472
00:36:03,536 --> 00:36:06,289
Get inside. It's okay.

473
00:36:10,126 --> 00:36:11,002
What the…

474
00:36:12,628 --> 00:36:16,465
It's already started? I thought she was
sending someone else instead of Pal-ho.

475
00:36:31,105 --> 00:36:32,273
Hey, Master.

476
00:36:32,773 --> 00:36:34,358
Are you mad at us or something?

477
00:36:35,026 --> 00:36:36,527
Let's talk it out.

478
00:36:37,111 --> 00:36:40,781
It's her. The one with the gloomy face
who brainwashes and uses people.

479
00:36:40,865 --> 00:36:43,868
She even made Mr. Gu
point a gun at Grandma earlier.

480
00:36:43,951 --> 00:36:44,994
Really?

481
00:37:02,386 --> 00:37:03,596
Chae-ni!

482
00:37:12,480 --> 00:37:13,314
Master.

483
00:37:46,681 --> 00:37:47,807
Master!

484
00:37:47,890 --> 00:37:48,975
Chae-ni!

485
00:37:56,649 --> 00:37:57,858
Chae-ni.

486
00:38:06,284 --> 00:38:08,035
Snap out of it, Choi Un-jeong!

487
00:38:21,549 --> 00:38:22,466
It's Lee Un-jeong.

488
00:38:25,636 --> 00:38:29,015
I thought
you were really going to kill me.

489
00:38:29,098 --> 00:38:31,851
How could you choke me so hard?

490
00:39:04,050 --> 00:39:06,010
- Cars flying around…
- Stop talking and…

491
00:39:06,552 --> 00:39:08,596
What the…

492
00:39:09,180 --> 00:39:10,348
Why won't you listen?

493
00:39:10,431 --> 00:39:11,640
What's with them?

494
00:39:11,724 --> 00:39:13,100
Why are they acting like that?

495
00:39:13,601 --> 00:39:15,311
Sir, where are you going?

496
00:39:17,730 --> 00:39:20,983
Don't worry. I'm sure
our shepherd left some instructions.

497
00:39:21,067 --> 00:39:21,984
- Really?
- He did?

498
00:39:22,068 --> 00:39:24,111
Why? What's up there?

499
00:39:24,195 --> 00:39:25,237
Where are you going?

500
00:39:25,321 --> 00:39:27,448
No! You can't go there.

501
00:39:27,531 --> 00:39:28,991
Where do you think you're going?

502
00:39:29,075 --> 00:39:30,701
- Must be that way.
- They're strange.

503
00:39:30,785 --> 00:39:32,203
- Should we go too?
- Shut it.

504
00:39:32,286 --> 00:39:33,662
Something's up with them.

505
00:40:03,484 --> 00:40:04,568
Chae-ni!

506
00:40:06,112 --> 00:40:07,196
Master!

507
00:40:33,305 --> 00:40:34,473
You two stay here.

508
00:40:34,557 --> 00:40:36,725
No matter what happens, don't come out.

509
00:40:36,809 --> 00:40:37,643
Am I clear?

510
00:40:37,726 --> 00:40:38,894
Are you insane?

511
00:40:39,645 --> 00:40:41,856
Where do you think you're going,
leaving us here?

512
00:40:41,939 --> 00:40:43,441
You have to protect us!

513
00:40:43,524 --> 00:40:45,776
I have to get out there to protect you.

514
00:40:45,860 --> 00:40:47,820
What could you do out there?

515
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:50,573
What can you do about a car flying at you?

516
00:40:51,073 --> 00:40:53,284
Think you can stop that
with your smart mouth?

517
00:40:53,367 --> 00:40:54,702
Good point.

518
00:40:55,202 --> 00:40:58,747
But it turns out there is something
I can do with my smart mouth.

519
00:41:02,585 --> 00:41:04,712
If you go out there now,

520
00:41:05,754 --> 00:41:06,964
I really will divorce you.

521
00:41:08,757 --> 00:41:10,593
I'm serious this time.

522
00:41:30,529 --> 00:41:32,198
No, honey!

523
00:42:07,233 --> 00:42:08,484
I love you,

524
00:42:09,276 --> 00:42:10,236
Mi-hui.

525
00:42:10,319 --> 00:42:11,946
You dummy!

526
00:42:22,957 --> 00:42:25,251
Mr. Son Gyeong-hun! What took you so long?

527
00:42:25,918 --> 00:42:29,088
I'll handle the side with more people.
You take that side, Mr. Kang.

528
00:42:29,171 --> 00:42:31,048
Can someone insult me?

529
00:42:31,131 --> 00:42:33,759
Are you going to rely on
someone insulting you forever?

530
00:42:33,842 --> 00:42:37,721
Why don't you try to drum up some strength
on your own, you oversized moron?

531
00:42:39,223 --> 00:42:40,224
They're coming.

532
00:43:04,456 --> 00:43:05,416
Isn't it fascinating?

533
00:43:07,751 --> 00:43:08,877
I'm scared!

534
00:43:24,518 --> 00:43:25,352
Get back!

535
00:43:33,819 --> 00:43:35,112
Hey, stay back!

536
00:43:39,867 --> 00:43:40,951
That wasn't me.

537
00:43:41,035 --> 00:43:42,286
I'm your father!

538
00:43:44,038 --> 00:43:45,706
I'm your mother!

539
00:44:20,532 --> 00:44:21,367
I'm sorry.

540
00:44:27,081 --> 00:44:29,249
No. Don't do it--

541
00:44:37,299 --> 00:44:38,342
Ma'am?

542
00:44:39,218 --> 00:44:40,260
Please insult me.

543
00:44:40,344 --> 00:44:41,261
What?

544
00:44:41,345 --> 00:44:42,471
Hurry.

545
00:44:43,972 --> 00:44:45,265
For crying out loud.

546
00:44:45,349 --> 00:44:48,227
How dare this rootless
good-for-nothing bastard

547
00:44:48,310 --> 00:44:50,896
show up out of nowhere
and act like a bumbling idiot!

548
00:44:50,979 --> 00:44:54,358
Should I pop your eyeballs out
and chew them up like radish kimchi?

549
00:44:54,441 --> 00:44:58,153
Why, I should gouge your eyes out
and suck the ink out of them dry.

550
00:44:58,237 --> 00:44:59,530
Want me to whoop your ass?

551
00:44:59,613 --> 00:45:02,366
You dirty bastard with shit for brains.

552
00:45:02,449 --> 00:45:03,826
Piss off, you rotten bastard!

553
00:45:43,323 --> 00:45:44,575
Bam!

554
00:45:46,452 --> 00:45:47,953
Honk honk!

555
00:45:55,294 --> 00:45:59,298
Anyone who wants to roll around
with me, stick here!

556
00:45:59,381 --> 00:46:01,341
This is so exciting!

557
00:46:02,843 --> 00:46:04,344
This is so much fun!

558
00:46:06,472 --> 00:46:08,974
Let's all go on a walk
Around the neighborhood

559
00:46:09,057 --> 00:46:12,144
Wake up early in the dead of night
Walk around the neighborhood

560
00:46:12,227 --> 00:46:14,980
Yang-soon says hello to us too

561
00:46:15,063 --> 00:46:18,317
We all say hello
As we walk around the neighborhood

562
00:46:22,029 --> 00:46:25,157
I swear, I've never…
You must be completely nuts.

563
00:46:25,240 --> 00:46:28,368
You and your shenanigans!

564
00:46:41,131 --> 00:46:42,090
We're back.

565
00:46:42,591 --> 00:46:43,717
That

566
00:46:44,343 --> 00:46:45,177
worked.

567
00:46:45,260 --> 00:46:46,553
Yeah.

568
00:46:47,054 --> 00:46:48,180
It worked.

569
00:46:48,263 --> 00:46:49,807
- Ouch.
- Mr. Son!

570
00:46:49,890 --> 00:46:51,558
Chae-ni! My goodness.

571
00:46:58,857 --> 00:46:59,691
Cheong.

572
00:47:00,275 --> 00:47:01,735
What did we

573
00:47:02,361 --> 00:47:03,529
just see?

574
00:47:04,363 --> 00:47:07,074
Superheroes?

575
00:47:17,251 --> 00:47:20,212
Is it time to clean up now?
Are you even listening?

576
00:47:20,295 --> 00:47:23,048
Did that really just happen?

577
00:47:23,549 --> 00:47:26,301
Or is this a prank show?
I didn't hear anything about it.

578
00:47:26,385 --> 00:47:30,514
That's why he was a special recruit.
For his superpower.

579
00:47:30,597 --> 00:47:33,058
I thought he'd hit his peak.

580
00:47:34,101 --> 00:47:36,311
To think he's even hotter than I thought.

581
00:47:37,938 --> 00:47:38,772
Un-jeong--

582
00:47:52,244 --> 00:47:55,372
I just hit them with this,
and the people over there…

583
00:48:10,345 --> 00:48:11,889
Look!

584
00:48:11,972 --> 00:48:13,265
Run!

585
00:48:13,348 --> 00:48:16,184
- Just run!
- Should we go down here?

586
00:48:23,317 --> 00:48:25,360
This really is endless.

587
00:48:26,528 --> 00:48:27,988
She's brainwashing them.

588
00:48:28,488 --> 00:48:30,532
This won't end unless we find her.

589
00:48:30,616 --> 00:48:32,492
No, we have to stop the fireworks first.

590
00:48:33,493 --> 00:48:37,122
There'll be fireworks at midnight,
and it's likely the drug is inside them.

591
00:48:37,205 --> 00:48:40,250
They'll gather people on the streets
for the countdown

592
00:48:40,334 --> 00:48:43,086
then, at midnight, with a single… boom!

593
00:48:47,090 --> 00:48:49,009
Midnight is less than 30 minutes away.

594
00:48:49,092 --> 00:48:50,010
So what do we do?

595
00:48:50,093 --> 00:48:52,471
Deal with the brainwashing woman first,
or the fireworks?

596
00:48:52,554 --> 00:48:54,431
I'll take care of the fireworks!

597
00:48:54,514 --> 00:48:55,724
Mr. Kang, you go with her.

598
00:48:55,807 --> 00:48:58,602
Mr. Son, you can find
the brainwashing woman.

599
00:48:58,685 --> 00:49:00,020
She must be nearby.

600
00:49:06,735 --> 00:49:07,694
Hurry!

601
00:49:13,367 --> 00:49:14,993
I am Spider-Man.

602
00:49:15,911 --> 00:49:17,287
I am a virgin ghost.

603
00:49:17,371 --> 00:49:19,289
I am Frankenstein.

604
00:49:19,790 --> 00:49:21,208
I'm the Hong Kong Granny Ghost.

605
00:49:22,042 --> 00:49:23,794
Oh my!

606
00:49:24,878 --> 00:49:26,046
Oh my goodness!

607
00:49:36,056 --> 00:49:38,058
Hurry, Ms. Eun Chae-ni.

608
00:49:53,573 --> 00:49:54,408
There it is.

609
00:49:54,491 --> 00:49:56,243
- Chae-ni.
- We're in the right place.

610
00:49:56,326 --> 00:49:57,452
Damn it.

611
00:50:05,585 --> 00:50:06,920
Damn.

612
00:50:32,487 --> 00:50:35,949
In these things here? Are these the drugs?
Where are the fireworks?

613
00:50:36,033 --> 00:50:36,950
I'll check these.

614
00:50:39,036 --> 00:50:40,078
Excuse me.

615
00:50:40,162 --> 00:50:41,830
- What are you doing?
- Who are you?

616
00:50:41,913 --> 00:50:43,582
Get out of there. It's dangerous.

617
00:50:43,665 --> 00:50:44,833
One second.

618
00:50:46,376 --> 00:50:47,210
What is it?

619
00:50:47,711 --> 00:50:49,254
Something strange in the sky.

620
00:51:17,532 --> 00:51:18,492
Goal!

621
00:51:26,249 --> 00:51:27,667
That's enough!

622
00:51:32,923 --> 00:51:33,757
Stop it.

623
00:51:36,426 --> 00:51:38,553
I said stop it! People are getting hurt!

624
00:51:38,637 --> 00:51:41,723
You may be in a cult,
but you're still meant to be a believer.

625
00:51:41,807 --> 00:51:43,391
You can't openly use violence.

626
00:51:44,392 --> 00:51:45,227
Can you hear me?

627
00:51:45,310 --> 00:51:48,313
Listen to me first, you little shit!

628
00:51:48,396 --> 00:51:52,442
Even if you're industry standard
and we're defective, this is wrong!

629
00:51:52,943 --> 00:51:56,363
How dare you use your superpowers
in such a godawful way!

630
00:51:56,446 --> 00:51:57,280
Can you hear--

631
00:51:57,364 --> 00:51:59,741
Again! There you go,
interrupting me again!

632
00:52:01,159 --> 00:52:04,454
How dare you keep interrupting
when an elder is talking to you!

633
00:52:05,080 --> 00:52:06,873
Where did you learn such bad manners?

634
00:52:06,957 --> 00:52:08,375
- Can you--
- I said stop!

635
00:52:08,458 --> 00:52:09,709
Just stop it!

636
00:52:10,710 --> 00:52:13,421
What did those people ever do to you
to deserve this?

637
00:52:13,922 --> 00:52:16,133
Sure, let's say
Trainwreck and Sap deserve it.

638
00:52:16,216 --> 00:52:18,343
What about me and Moon Mi-hui? And Cheong?

639
00:52:18,426 --> 00:52:20,887
And all those other miscellaneous people.

640
00:52:20,971 --> 00:52:23,932
What did they ever do to you
to deserve this? Why?

641
00:52:24,516 --> 00:52:25,600
What's the reason?

642
00:52:29,354 --> 00:52:32,607
People didn't care about
the pain we endured.

643
00:52:33,316 --> 00:52:34,192
No interest at all.

644
00:52:35,152 --> 00:52:36,903
So I don't care either,

645
00:52:37,487 --> 00:52:38,905
whether or not they die.

646
00:52:41,283 --> 00:52:43,076
Never been scolded by an elder, right?

647
00:52:44,494 --> 00:52:47,873
Well, you picked the wrong person
to mess with today.

648
00:52:47,956 --> 00:52:51,209
I'm going to finally drill some manners
into you today--

649
00:52:56,089 --> 00:52:57,048
You little…

650
00:53:15,567 --> 00:53:16,526
Ju-ran.

651
00:53:35,962 --> 00:53:36,963
What happened?

652
00:53:37,464 --> 00:53:38,298
Are you okay?

653
00:53:59,569 --> 00:54:01,488
Ju-ran, are you okay?

654
00:54:06,117 --> 00:54:08,286
Why did you push yourself like this?

655
00:54:08,787 --> 00:54:10,830
You told us
not to use our powers recklessly.

656
00:54:12,207 --> 00:54:13,875
Pal-ho is dead.

657
00:54:16,962 --> 00:54:18,838
And so is Father.

658
00:54:31,643 --> 00:54:33,520
Let's stop this now.

659
00:54:35,981 --> 00:54:38,858
I don't want to lose you too, okay?

660
00:54:40,235 --> 00:54:42,070
I can't forgive them.

661
00:54:42,654 --> 00:54:44,489
I'll kill them all.

662
00:54:47,325 --> 00:54:48,451
You still have me.

663
00:54:50,078 --> 00:54:53,290
We have no one left, Ho-ran.

664
00:54:54,582 --> 00:54:55,917
Avenge us.

665
00:54:57,043 --> 00:54:58,378
All of them.

666
00:54:59,254 --> 00:55:00,922
Destroy them all.

667
00:55:04,801 --> 00:55:06,928
Please do that for me, Ho-ran.

668
00:55:30,327 --> 00:55:31,411
Here they come.

669
00:55:32,746 --> 00:55:33,955
Hey, are you okay?

670
00:55:34,039 --> 00:55:35,040
No.

671
00:55:35,123 --> 00:55:37,125
- My head hurts.
- Earlier, you were all…

672
00:55:37,208 --> 00:55:39,627
They've snapped out of it.

673
00:55:40,795 --> 00:55:42,088
Is it over or what?

674
00:56:07,530 --> 00:56:08,698
Are you hurt badly?

675
00:56:10,784 --> 00:56:12,202
I'm just a bit tired.

676
00:56:21,628 --> 00:56:23,838
What happened with the fireworks?

677
00:56:27,175 --> 00:56:28,635
You won't be able to stop it.

678
00:56:30,762 --> 00:56:31,596
Ms. Eun Chae-ni?

679
00:56:40,105 --> 00:56:41,981
It'll be so very pretty.

680
00:56:43,650 --> 00:56:45,110
The truth is,

681
00:56:46,111 --> 00:56:48,405
I've never seen fireworks
in person either.

682
00:57:00,125 --> 00:57:01,709
My final goodbye.

683
00:57:09,259 --> 00:57:14,806
All right,
there really isn't much left of 1999.

684
00:57:14,889 --> 00:57:20,437
Are you all spending the last moments
of the 20th century with your loved ones?

685
00:57:20,937 --> 00:57:26,901
There are about five minutes left
until the new millennium begins.

686
00:57:26,985 --> 00:57:31,906
I'm hoping you're all spending
these last few minutes of 1999

687
00:57:31,990 --> 00:57:35,452
with the people you cherish most.

688
00:57:35,994 --> 00:57:39,414
This is the last song I'm playing for you
in the 20th century.

689
00:58:08,443 --> 00:58:11,529
This is the price
of our shepherd Kim Pal-ho's blood.

690
00:58:27,295 --> 00:58:28,671
Chae-ni!

691
00:58:28,755 --> 00:58:30,173
Why, is something wrong?

692
00:58:32,967 --> 00:58:34,260
Why? What is it?

693
00:58:36,846 --> 00:58:38,765
Are you really Eun Chae-ni?

694
00:58:38,848 --> 00:58:40,433
Of course I'm Eun Chae-ni.

695
00:58:40,517 --> 00:58:42,685
Who else would I be, Geum Chae-ni?
What is it?

696
00:58:44,479 --> 00:58:45,480
There…

697
00:58:49,859 --> 00:58:51,861
There's another Chae-ni!

698
00:58:53,446 --> 00:58:54,739
Why am I over there?

699
00:58:56,950 --> 00:58:58,618
Did I just get stabbed?

700
00:58:59,118 --> 00:58:59,953
No!

701
00:59:05,917 --> 00:59:06,876
What's this?

702
00:59:24,269 --> 00:59:27,647
Breathe. I need you to stay awake.
I'll call an ambulance.

703
00:59:28,231 --> 00:59:29,148
Are you…

704
00:59:31,401 --> 00:59:33,152
worrying about me?

705
00:59:35,738 --> 00:59:36,573
Yeah.

706
00:59:42,078 --> 00:59:43,621
- Look at that!
- Wow.

707
00:59:43,705 --> 00:59:44,706
Just like you did

708
00:59:45,373 --> 00:59:46,624
for me back then.

709
00:59:46,708 --> 00:59:48,459
Wow, look at that fish!

710
00:59:48,543 --> 00:59:50,378
You didn't just comfort me,

711
00:59:51,129 --> 00:59:53,381
you comforted all the kids in there.

712
00:59:53,464 --> 00:59:54,674
There are so many!

713
00:59:57,885 --> 00:59:58,970
It…

714
01:00:02,265 --> 01:00:03,891
would have been nice…

715
01:00:06,728 --> 01:00:08,062
if you'd been on my side.

716
01:00:22,910 --> 01:00:23,828
No.

717
01:00:24,871 --> 01:00:25,830
No.

718
01:00:26,748 --> 01:00:27,874
Ho-ran.

719
01:00:29,292 --> 01:00:30,793
No!

720
01:00:33,838 --> 01:00:36,341
Is she dead? Is she really?

721
01:00:36,424 --> 01:00:39,510
Her pulse is still there.
Can you call an ambulance?

722
01:00:40,428 --> 01:00:43,473
Damn it, I think I dropped
my cell phone somewhere. Hold on.

723
01:00:44,724 --> 01:00:47,310
Ro-bin, let's move her inside first.

724
01:00:48,436 --> 01:00:50,063
Where could I have dropped…

725
01:00:53,107 --> 01:00:54,484
Honey, where are you going?

726
01:00:55,526 --> 01:00:56,361
Honey!

727
01:00:56,444 --> 01:00:59,113
I told you not to come out
until I told you to.

728
01:00:59,197 --> 01:01:01,032
Honey, where are you going?

729
01:01:19,842 --> 01:01:20,843
What is that?

730
01:01:36,234 --> 01:01:43,241
THE JUDGE IS STANDING AT THE DOOR
JAMES 5:9

731
01:02:15,022 --> 01:02:16,899
You won't be able to stop it.

732
01:02:21,362 --> 01:02:24,949
The prophecy will be fulfilled as planned.

733
01:02:26,367 --> 01:02:28,369
You will know when the apocalypse comes.

734
01:02:29,412 --> 01:02:31,164
Those who do not believe

735
01:02:31,664 --> 01:02:34,876
will be cast into the hellfire
known as death.

736
01:02:36,085 --> 01:02:38,254
As for those who are saved,

737
01:02:38,755 --> 01:02:42,925
they will gain eternal life
as Wunderkinder!

738
01:02:57,231 --> 01:02:59,567
So that was the real bomb.

739
01:03:02,028 --> 01:03:03,654
It wasn't the fireworks?

740
01:03:36,938 --> 01:03:39,982
Maybe it was never
something we could stop.

741
01:04:19,480 --> 01:04:22,191
I said I wanted to live
to see the apocalypse.

742
01:04:22,900 --> 01:04:24,986
I guess my wish came true.

743
01:04:28,739 --> 01:04:30,366
But what a shame.

744
01:04:33,202 --> 01:04:35,288
I no longer want to see

745
01:04:35,997 --> 01:04:37,582
this goddamn apocalypse.

746
01:04:39,542 --> 01:04:42,128
Chae-ni, what are you saying?
You're making me nervous.

747
01:04:43,045 --> 01:04:47,049
Ro-bin, toss me and Mr. Son up there.

748
01:04:48,301 --> 01:04:49,552
Why me?

749
01:04:49,635 --> 01:04:51,762
There's nowhere to hold on to.

750
01:04:51,846 --> 01:04:54,599
Just stick me on securely,
then you can fall off.

751
01:04:54,682 --> 01:04:57,018
I'll try to teleport with that airship.

752
01:04:57,894 --> 01:05:00,354
And what if something terrible
happens to you?

753
01:05:00,438 --> 01:05:02,982
Don't worry.
You know that I don't die, even if I do.

754
01:05:03,065 --> 01:05:07,236
Why would you not die? Don't you know
how that heart ended up with you?

755
01:05:08,613 --> 01:05:11,616
If anything goes wrong, that heart
could be all that's left of you.

756
01:05:11,699 --> 01:05:13,492
That's a bomb, you doofus.

757
01:05:13,576 --> 01:05:15,786
If it explodes,
you'd be blown to smithereens.

758
01:05:15,870 --> 01:05:17,413
What would we say to Grandma?

759
01:05:17,496 --> 01:05:21,417
It'd be a secret, of course.
Don't tell her, Kang Ro-bin, okay?

760
01:05:21,500 --> 01:05:23,127
I'll be back soon.

761
01:05:23,210 --> 01:05:24,045
No.

762
01:05:24,712 --> 01:05:27,173
Then let's go together.
I'll go up there with you.

763
01:05:28,841 --> 01:05:29,675
In your state?

764
01:05:31,218 --> 01:05:33,262
You'll just be a burden, okay?

765
01:05:33,346 --> 01:05:36,432
Just make sure to catch us when we fall.

766
01:05:36,515 --> 01:05:39,060
Catch Mr. Son first. Then me.

767
01:05:39,143 --> 01:05:40,436
Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

768
01:05:41,938 --> 01:05:45,066
You know I could die
if I fall from that height, don't you?

769
01:05:45,900 --> 01:05:48,194
So I'm asking you to catch me.

770
01:05:48,277 --> 01:05:51,989
It would be a darn shame
to die after completing the mission, no?

771
01:05:55,952 --> 01:05:57,703
Hurry up. We don't have much time.

772
01:05:59,830 --> 01:06:01,082
It'll be okay.

773
01:06:12,468 --> 01:06:13,302
Okay.

774
01:06:18,140 --> 01:06:19,183
Let's do it.

775
01:06:20,601 --> 01:06:21,477
Why the hell not?

776
01:06:27,108 --> 01:06:28,234
You look pretty today.

777
01:06:30,486 --> 01:06:31,779
It's done.

778
01:06:35,032 --> 01:06:36,075
You know what, Ro-bin?

779
01:06:37,201 --> 01:06:39,036
You're fugly when you smile.

780
01:06:41,455 --> 01:06:43,374
Eun Chae-ni, I swear, you…

781
01:06:43,457 --> 01:06:45,167
Just toss us already, King Sap!

782
01:06:45,251 --> 01:06:46,460
You Sappy Sap!

783
01:06:53,592 --> 01:06:55,761
King Sap!

784
01:07:18,617 --> 01:07:19,535
I

785
01:07:20,828 --> 01:07:22,163
want Eun Chae-ni

786
01:07:22,872 --> 01:07:24,790
to just

787
01:07:25,374 --> 01:07:26,375
disappear

788
01:07:26,459 --> 01:07:28,753
forever!

789
01:07:29,253 --> 01:07:30,296
- Go!
- What?

790
01:07:30,379 --> 01:07:31,797
You need to climb up.

791
01:07:31,881 --> 01:07:33,424
Come on. Go a little further!

792
01:07:33,507 --> 01:07:34,550
You go!

793
01:07:36,427 --> 01:07:37,803
Wait, one second.

794
01:07:37,887 --> 01:07:38,929
Just a bit more.

795
01:07:39,013 --> 01:07:40,056
Don't fall off yet.

796
01:07:40,139 --> 01:07:41,182
- Go!
- Stay stuck.

797
01:07:41,265 --> 01:07:42,224
Go!

798
01:07:42,308 --> 01:07:44,727
- Go!
- Wait a minute, Mr. Son.

799
01:07:45,227 --> 01:07:46,353
Ow, easy!

800
01:07:56,197 --> 01:07:57,364
I'm up.

801
01:07:57,948 --> 01:08:01,035
Mr. Son, you should go now!

802
01:08:01,118 --> 01:08:04,413
You were really impressive today.

803
01:08:05,247 --> 01:08:06,165
Hey.

804
01:08:07,500 --> 01:08:08,626
Do good, you punk!

805
01:08:16,550 --> 01:08:17,885
Still,

806
01:08:18,552 --> 01:08:22,640
I hope Eun Chae-ni comes back
safe and sound!

807
01:09:18,779 --> 01:09:22,241
All right,
we really don't have much time left now.

808
01:09:22,324 --> 01:09:25,244
Let's start the countdown.

809
01:09:26,829 --> 01:09:27,663
Ten,

810
01:09:28,330 --> 01:09:29,165
nine,

811
01:09:30,249 --> 01:09:31,125
eight,

812
01:09:31,917 --> 01:09:32,751
seven,

813
01:09:33,419 --> 01:09:34,253
six,

814
01:09:35,087 --> 01:09:36,005
five,

815
01:09:36,589 --> 01:09:37,548
four,

816
01:09:38,048 --> 01:09:39,049
three,

817
01:09:39,758 --> 01:09:40,843
two,

818
01:09:40,926 --> 01:09:41,927
one!

819
01:10:13,626 --> 01:10:14,460
Eunie.

820
01:10:25,679 --> 01:10:27,473
The year 2000!

821
01:10:27,556 --> 01:10:30,976
The new millennium has finally begun.

822
01:10:39,902 --> 01:10:40,819
No.

823
01:10:43,072 --> 01:10:43,989
No!

824
01:10:45,115 --> 01:10:47,284
No!

825
01:11:06,303 --> 01:11:07,221
Where am I?

826
01:11:07,304 --> 01:11:08,722
- What is that?
- In the sky!

827
01:11:10,474 --> 01:11:12,101
What happened?

828
01:11:26,407 --> 01:11:29,326
I should be watching this with Cheong.

829
01:11:34,498 --> 01:11:35,874
What a view!

830
01:11:45,342 --> 01:11:46,760
We stopped it.

831
01:11:47,511 --> 01:11:48,721
We

832
01:11:50,264 --> 01:11:52,391
saved these people.

833
01:11:53,350 --> 01:11:55,227
When Chae-ni comes back,

834
01:11:56,937 --> 01:11:58,897
please make sure you catch her, Master.

835
01:11:59,940 --> 01:12:00,774
Yeah.

836
01:12:12,745 --> 01:12:14,705
She's late. Did she go somewhere far?

837
01:12:15,205 --> 01:12:17,499
Did she go to Canada again?

838
01:12:19,626 --> 01:12:24,173
Even if she went to the North Pole,
not Canada,

839
01:12:24,256 --> 01:12:27,760
she should've been back by now
because she'd be teleporting.

840
01:12:28,344 --> 01:12:29,219
Damn it.

841
01:12:30,179 --> 01:12:31,889
Stop saying dumb stuff.

842
01:13:00,125 --> 01:13:03,837
And so, the year 2000 began
with nothing out of the ordinary.

843
01:13:04,338 --> 01:13:08,008
Finally, the new millennium has begun.

844
01:13:08,592 --> 01:13:13,097
With the start of the year 2000,
we have some news of an incident.

845
01:13:13,597 --> 01:13:17,184
Last night,
a sudden squall occurred in Haeseong.

846
01:13:17,267 --> 01:13:18,727
During its Millennium Festival…

847
01:13:18,811 --> 01:13:22,064
My goodness,
what kind of squall flips over cars?

848
01:13:24,566 --> 01:13:27,027
And it ruined the parade too.

849
01:13:27,611 --> 01:13:30,030
Still, Cheong looks great
in these pictures.

850
01:13:32,366 --> 01:13:33,951
Do you really not remember?

851
01:13:34,451 --> 01:13:38,414
Do you really not remember how cool I was
when I saved you two that day?

852
01:13:38,497 --> 01:13:41,333
I took you to shelter in the record store.

853
01:13:41,417 --> 01:13:44,294
And then I saved people and stuff,
you know?

854
01:13:44,378 --> 01:13:46,547
Now you're resorting to telling
outlandish lies?

855
01:13:49,133 --> 01:13:52,261
Why not just say you flew around
with a cape on?

856
01:13:52,761 --> 01:13:54,555
I'm so sick of you.

857
01:13:59,560 --> 01:14:00,686
- Dad.
- Yeah?

858
01:14:00,769 --> 01:14:02,438
- My lunch box.
- Didn't I give it to you?

859
01:14:02,521 --> 01:14:03,605
There it is.

860
01:14:07,609 --> 01:14:09,528
They are absolutely ridiculous.

861
01:14:09,611 --> 01:14:10,737
Unbelievable…

862
01:14:12,656 --> 01:14:16,952
And no one remembered the events
that took place that day.

863
01:14:17,661 --> 01:14:18,745
A squall?

864
01:14:18,829 --> 01:14:21,081
How could a squall blow a car away?

865
01:14:21,165 --> 01:14:22,249
Tell me about it.

866
01:14:22,332 --> 01:14:23,542
How did you get this?

867
01:14:25,419 --> 01:14:26,253
What the…

868
01:14:27,129 --> 01:14:28,839
Why doesn't anyone remember?

869
01:14:30,340 --> 01:14:31,467
Could it be…

870
01:14:34,720 --> 01:14:35,804
Honey.

871
01:14:36,513 --> 01:14:37,764
Honey!

872
01:14:38,265 --> 01:14:39,141
Honey!

873
01:14:40,976 --> 01:14:42,352
Why are you standing there?

874
01:14:46,690 --> 01:14:49,401
Honey, yes, it's me.

875
01:14:54,114 --> 01:14:56,992
I saved you and Cheong,

876
01:14:57,493 --> 01:14:59,036
and I saved everyone.

877
01:15:00,162 --> 01:15:01,246
What are you on about?

878
01:15:02,706 --> 01:15:06,043
I don't see Cheong. Go and find her.

879
01:15:06,126 --> 01:15:07,628
Cheong!

880
01:15:08,670 --> 01:15:10,047
Son Cheong!

881
01:15:11,173 --> 01:15:13,008
No, I saved you…

882
01:15:14,092 --> 01:15:15,594
We did it!

883
01:15:16,094 --> 01:15:17,804
We saved you and Haeseong

884
01:15:18,722 --> 01:15:20,807
from the apocalypse!

885
01:15:20,891 --> 01:15:22,643
So why don't you remember?

886
01:15:27,523 --> 01:15:29,316
For some unknown reason,

887
01:15:30,150 --> 01:15:33,195
the heroes of that day
disappeared from everyone's memories.

888
01:15:33,278 --> 01:15:34,446
Why?

889
01:15:35,239 --> 01:15:37,658
Why do you all look so clueless?

890
01:15:38,325 --> 01:15:42,287
For God's sake! Do you really think
this car flipped over from a squall?

891
01:15:42,371 --> 01:15:43,497
But

892
01:15:44,331 --> 01:15:45,332
I…

893
01:15:46,083 --> 01:15:47,459
My darling daughter.

894
01:15:47,960 --> 01:15:50,379
Have a good day today too, okay?

895
01:15:51,755 --> 01:15:53,131
You did great, Dad.

896
01:15:53,215 --> 01:15:54,091
Yeah.

897
01:15:55,968 --> 01:15:56,969
What?

898
01:16:01,848 --> 01:16:03,475
Yeah, thanks, Cheong.

899
01:16:09,940 --> 01:16:11,608
Thank you, honey.

900
01:16:19,032 --> 01:16:22,494
HEARTY HOUSE

901
01:16:26,707 --> 01:16:28,375
She'll come back.

902
01:16:29,459 --> 01:16:31,461
My baby will come back, yes.

903
01:16:32,546 --> 01:16:33,714
She just went too far,

904
01:16:34,840 --> 01:16:37,134
so she's taking a while
to find her way back.

905
01:16:38,135 --> 01:16:38,969
Well…

906
01:16:40,846 --> 01:16:42,598
that's possible, isn't it?

907
01:16:43,098 --> 01:16:43,932
Yeah.

908
01:17:37,069 --> 01:17:41,531
FLORALA

909
01:18:00,217 --> 01:18:01,551
Those little shits.

910
01:18:16,900 --> 01:18:18,735
They say you have to make a grave,

911
01:18:18,819 --> 01:18:22,197
even if it's empty,
for someone who died away from home.

912
01:18:24,282 --> 01:18:28,120
So that their soul doesn't wander
the netherworld aimlessly.

913
01:18:53,019 --> 01:18:54,688
MEMORIAL TABLET
EUN CHAE-NI

914
01:19:03,488 --> 01:19:04,906
Enjoy.

915
01:19:07,534 --> 01:19:09,244
Please enjoy.

916
01:19:11,580 --> 01:19:14,416
Not much to eat here.
What kind of party is this?

917
01:19:15,000 --> 01:19:16,710
You shouldn't eat with your hands.

918
01:19:16,793 --> 01:19:18,545
Then hurry up with the serving.

919
01:19:18,628 --> 01:19:21,089
Sorry, we're just giving out
generous portions.

920
01:19:21,173 --> 01:19:23,884
If you're starved, come here.
I'll serve you first.

921
01:19:29,848 --> 01:19:31,600
Is this for a 49-day ritual?

922
01:19:32,100 --> 01:19:33,185
Did someone die?

923
01:19:33,685 --> 01:19:35,228
Who died?

924
01:19:37,439 --> 01:19:38,398
You…

925
01:19:40,901 --> 01:19:41,943
You…

926
01:19:42,444 --> 01:19:43,278
Eunie.

927
01:19:44,196 --> 01:19:45,530
Is that you, Eunie?

928
01:19:46,531 --> 01:19:47,574
Chae-ni!

929
01:19:48,658 --> 01:19:49,785
You mean Eun Chae-ni?

930
01:19:49,868 --> 01:19:50,827
Goodness!

931
01:19:53,413 --> 01:19:54,581
Goodness gracious!

932
01:19:55,582 --> 01:19:56,500
Good heavens!

933
01:19:57,000 --> 01:19:58,919
My goodness, Chae-ni.

934
01:20:04,341 --> 01:20:06,885
Let me look at you. My goodness.

935
01:20:06,968 --> 01:20:09,721
It took me a while to get back, didn't it?

936
01:20:10,222 --> 01:20:13,433
I tried to go
to the furthest place I knew,

937
01:20:13,517 --> 01:20:16,144
and I ended up in a desert
on the other side of the planet.

938
01:20:16,228 --> 01:20:18,355
And I guess it was too far away

939
01:20:18,438 --> 01:20:20,440
because I couldn't make my way back.

940
01:20:20,524 --> 01:20:22,067
I had no passport, no money.

941
01:20:22,150 --> 01:20:26,321
So the journey back here
was absolutely grueling.

942
01:20:26,863 --> 01:20:29,407
But who died? Everyone's here.

943
01:20:29,491 --> 01:20:32,118
- My baby isn't dead.
- Who?

944
01:20:33,161 --> 01:20:34,788
My baby isn't dead, is she?

945
01:20:35,288 --> 01:20:37,415
My baby's alive!

946
01:20:43,004 --> 01:20:44,506
Wait.

947
01:20:44,589 --> 01:20:47,300
Wait, I'm starving, okay?
Give me some food first.

948
01:20:47,384 --> 01:20:48,718
- Food.
- Right, food.

949
01:20:49,386 --> 01:20:50,720
You brat!

950
01:20:51,304 --> 01:20:53,431
How can you be so unfazed?

951
01:20:53,515 --> 01:20:55,600
Do you know how sad we were?

952
01:20:55,684 --> 01:20:59,271
I knew better than anyone
that I wasn't dead,

953
01:20:59,354 --> 01:21:00,856
so why would I be sad?

954
01:21:01,481 --> 01:21:02,482
Is that so?

955
01:21:02,566 --> 01:21:04,150
I guess you're right!

956
01:21:07,070 --> 01:21:09,114
Can we get a wet towel here?

957
01:21:10,282 --> 01:21:11,741
You stinky little shit.

958
01:21:12,742 --> 01:21:14,870
I do stink, don't I? Have you been good?

959
01:21:17,956 --> 01:21:19,207
Food.

960
01:21:20,041 --> 01:21:21,418
Oh, my baby.

961
01:21:21,918 --> 01:21:23,295
The rice cakes are good today.

962
01:22:02,417 --> 01:22:04,169
Aren't you happy to see me, Master?

963
01:22:06,755 --> 01:22:07,923
What took you so long?

964
01:22:10,800 --> 01:22:13,887
It took me a while
to get used to being a stowaway.

965
01:22:14,763 --> 01:22:17,265
Why? Did you miss me?

966
01:22:20,226 --> 01:22:23,730
It was a refreshing change,
not having someone cling to me.

967
01:22:28,777 --> 01:22:29,653
Stay back, you.

968
01:22:33,323 --> 01:22:36,076
You try not washing for three weeks.
I bet you'd smell worse!

969
01:22:37,035 --> 01:22:39,204
Let's meet again after you've washed up.

970
01:22:47,003 --> 01:22:49,381
You won't be able to wash this off
with a shower.

971
01:22:49,881 --> 01:22:52,258
It'll last a whole week.

972
01:22:57,222 --> 01:22:58,306
You're…

973
01:23:00,058 --> 01:23:01,726
such a pain, Ms. Eun Chae-ni.

974
01:23:04,187 --> 01:23:05,105
I like you.

975
01:24:12,213 --> 01:24:13,923
Some people are different.

976
01:24:16,301 --> 01:24:18,636
Others are late bloomers.

977
01:24:20,346 --> 01:24:21,431
Others

978
01:24:22,223 --> 01:24:25,018
prefer the quiet outskirts.

979
01:24:25,769 --> 01:24:27,437
HAESEONG CITY HALL

980
01:24:27,520 --> 01:24:28,980
But

981
01:24:29,814 --> 01:24:31,941
there's no such thing

982
01:24:32,859 --> 01:24:34,194
as a nobody.

983
01:25:43,304 --> 01:25:45,807
- Yes?
- Is it done yet?

984
01:25:46,307 --> 01:25:48,226
No, just a moment.

985
01:25:49,018 --> 01:25:50,895
Just bring me what you have so far.

986
01:25:50,979 --> 01:25:51,813
Okay.

987
01:25:54,023 --> 01:25:56,317
Oh, for crying out loud.

988
01:25:56,401 --> 01:25:58,278
I told you to go back to Seoul!

989
01:25:58,361 --> 01:26:00,822
I don't know why you're still here,
driving me nuts.

990
01:26:00,905 --> 01:26:02,699
Next time, I'll do it all.

991
01:26:03,324 --> 01:26:05,034
Here, get this done quickly.

992
01:26:05,952 --> 01:26:08,079
CHURCH OF ETERNAL SALVATION

993
01:26:08,163 --> 01:26:11,124
Yes, the entrance has been blocked off.

994
01:26:11,708 --> 01:26:14,252
- Anything left?
- It's all charred.

995
01:26:18,590 --> 01:26:19,674
Search every inch.

996
01:26:19,757 --> 01:26:21,926
And report to me if you find anything.

997
01:26:22,010 --> 01:26:22,844
Yes, sir.

998
01:30:05,775 --> 01:30:10,780
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi
